这些 填空 并 不是 随意 在 文章 中 挖 一个 或 几个 词 得来 的 ， 而是 我们 觉得 值得注意 的


Flying   Cats
Cats     ( 1 )     [ 总是 ]   ( 2 )   [ 让 ∽ 琶 註   human   beings .   They   can   be   friendly   and
( 3 )     [ 对人 充满 感情 ] ,     but     they     ( 4 )     [ 过 着 神秘 的 生活 ]   of   their   own   as
well .   They   never   become   ( 5 )   [ 顺从 ]   like   dogs   and   horses .   ( 6 )   [ 结果 是 ] ,
humans     have     learned     to     respect     feline   ( 7 )   [ 独立性 ] .   Most   cats   ( 8 )
[ 对 ⌒ 拇 婊 骋 蒥   humans   all   their   lives .   One   of   the   things   that   ( 2 )   [ 让 …
着迷 ]     us     most     about     cats   is   the   popular   belief   that   they   have   nine
lives .     Apparently ,     there     is     a     great   deal   of   truth   in   this   idea .   A
cat ’ s   ability   to   ( 9 )   [ 摔 而 不 死 ]   is   based   on   fact .
Recently     the     New     York   Animal   Medical   Centre   made   a   study   of   132
cats     ( 10 )     [ 为期 五个 月 ] .     All   these   cats   ( 11 )   [ 有 一个 共同 的 纠 鷀 :   they
had       fallen       off     high     buildings ,     yet     only     eight     of     them     ( 12 )
[ 死 于 冲击 或 受伤 ] .     Of     course ,   New   York   is   the   ideal   place   for   such   an
interesting     study ,   because   there   is   ( 13 )   [ 不缺 ]   tall   buildings .   There
are     plenty     of     high - rise   windowsills   to   fall   from !   One   cat ,   Sabrina ,
fell     32   storeys ,   yet   only   suffered   from   a   broken   tooth .   ‘ Cats   behave
like     ( 14 )     [ 训练有素 的 ]     paratroopers , ’   a   doctor   said .   It   seems   that
the     further   cats   fall ,   ( 15 )   [ 它们 越 不大可能 伤 到 自己 ] .   In   a   long   drop ,
they     reach     speeds     of     60     miles     an   hour   and   more .   ( 16 )   [ 在 高速 中 ] ,
falling     cats     have     time     to     relax .   They   stretch   out   their   legs   like
flying     squirrels .   This   increases   their   air - resistance   and   reduces   the
shock   of   impact   when   they   hit   the   ground .

